[A new update on avian influenza in animals in Asia, issued by the Office
International des Epizooties (OIE) on 11 Feb 2004, may be seen at
<http://oie.int/downld/AVIAN%20INFLUENZA/A_AI-Asia.htmText>. It includes
the official follow-up report No. 1 of the Chinese Veterinary Services,
titled "Information of Highly Pathogenic Avian Influenza (HPAI) in
Mainland, P. R. China". According to this report, issued on 10 Feb 2004, up
to 2 Feb 2004 there have been a total of 38 outbreaks of the disease in 14
provinces (autonomous regions or municipalities), 23 of which have been
confirmed by the National Avian Influenza Reference Laboratory as subtype
H5N1-caused HPAI; the rest 15 being suspected cases. - Mod.AS]
